This paper is primarily focused on the security analysis of the OpenID Connect protocol, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses security guidelines for implementors, which could be considered under software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). Additionally, the paper discusses attacks and security measures related to web-based authentication, which could be categorized under cyber security (cs.CY) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
